{"TopicId":171645,"ForumId":32,"TopicTitle":"going into orbit","CreatedByName":"mardi","CreatedById":186048,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T03:56:36Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"mardi","CreatedById":186048,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T03:56:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis it is easier to orbit the sun or kerbal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Vanamonde","CreatedById":27914,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T05:01:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe home planet requires much, MUCH, \u003Cem\u003EMUCH \u003C/em\u003Eless \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E to reach. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure what you mean by your question, though. What are you trying to do?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jas0n","CreatedById":57441,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T17:34:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean... technically if you have enough fuel you can just go straight up from launch and end up in a sun orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eddiew","CreatedById":127483,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T17:46:36Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310034\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520184899\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 minutes ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean... technically if you have enough fuel you can just go straight up from launch and end up in a sun orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes... but the delta-v required to get out of Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESoI\u003C/abbr\u003E this way is more than to get into orbit around Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRule of thumb; straight up is never the cheap answer. You\u00A0lose 10m/s per second as the planet pulls you back, and when you\u0027re talking multi-minute burn times, it quickly becomes enormous. Gravity is a cruel mistress\u00A0\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-03-04T17:48:16Z\u0022 title=\u002203/04/2018 05:48  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 4, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by eddiew\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jas0n","CreatedById":57441,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T17:48:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310039\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520185596\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYes... but the delta-v required to get out of Kerbin\u0027s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESoI\u003C/abbr\u003E this way is more than to get into orbit around Kerbin.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRule of thumb; straight up is never the cheap answer ever. You constantly lose 10m/s per second. Gravity is cruel \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nharder in terms of delta-v, easier in terms piloting.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mardi","CreatedById":186048,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T18:19:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223309713\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520139670\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002227914\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Vanamonde\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 hours ago, Vanamonde said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe home planet requires much, MUCH, \u003Cem\u003EMUCH \u003C/em\u003Eless \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Delta-V\u0022\u003EdV\u003C/abbr\u003E to reach. \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNot sure what you mean by your question, though. What are you trying to do?\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\ntrying to orbit kerban for spying on my self\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T18:27:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310041\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520185725\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n31 minutes ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nharder in terms of delta-v, easier in terms piloting.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFrom a launch, it is MUCH easier to orbit the Sun.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBuild a rocket, fairly big, but doesn\u0027t have to be huge.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPoint straight up.\u00A0 Turn on \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Stability Augmentation System\u0022\u003ESAS\u003C/abbr\u003E.\u00A0 Fire engines.\u00A0 Keep going till you enter Solar orbit.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOrbiting Kerbin, on the other hand, takes a lot more finesse.\u00A0 Gravity turns, orital manuevering, controlled burns, etc.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223309670\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520135796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022186048\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mardi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 hours ago, mardi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis it is easier to orbit the sun or kerbal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe word \u0022easiest\u0022 is quite ambiguous in this situation, you\u0027ll have to clarify what you mean.\u00A0 Easier could mean less work (Solar), or cheaper rockets (Kerbal).\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"eddiew","CreatedById":127483,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T18:58:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310041\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520185725\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257441\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jas0n\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Jas0n said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nharder in terms of delta-v, easier in terms piloting.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027d argue that you\u0027d spend more time in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E making a rocket that will break \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESoI\u003C/abbr\u003E by going straight up than you will waste by pressing w a few times during the ascent of a smaller rocket \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso it\u0027s really hard to do anything useful with the resulting solar orbit unless your astro-fu is very strong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T19:26:25Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310091\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520189905\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n27 minutes ago, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAlso it\u0027s really hard to do anything useful with the resulting solar orbit unless your astro-fu is very strong.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nVery true!\u00A0 But that is part B of the question, and it wasn\u0027t asked \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"322997am","CreatedById":146422,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-04T19:40:28Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are inspired, then aim directly for the sun, and eventually your wings will be fried, and you will crash down into the ocean. My plane named icarus did this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"suicidejunkie","CreatedById":155878,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-05T17:48:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310116\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520192428\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022146422\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022322997am\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n22 hours ago, 322997am said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are inspired, then aim directly for the sun, and eventually your wings will be fried, and you will crash down into the ocean. My plane named icarus did this\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPSA: Do not aim vessels directly towards the sun.\u00A0 Burn orbital retrograde relative to the sun instead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Hans Dorn","CreatedById":105419,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-06T19:47:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223309670\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520135796\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022186048\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mardi\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4.3.2018 at 4:56 AM, mardi said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nis it is easier to orbit the sun or kerbal?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, technically speaking, you\u0027re already orbiting the sun while sitting on the launch pad \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"KevinW42","CreatedById":66949,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-07T00:36:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310885\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520272099\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022155878\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022suicidejunkie\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/5/2018 at 9:48 AM, suicidejunkie said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPSA: Do not aim vessels directly towards the sun.\u00A0 Burn orbital retrograde relative to the sun instead.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOr burn prograde relative to the sun until your apoapsis is really high, then burn retrograde there. Waaaaay less delta v.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gargamel","CreatedById":64714,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-07T02:43:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223311751\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520365666\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022105419\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Hans Dorn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, Hans Dorn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, technically speaking, you\u0027re already orbiting the sun while sitting on the launch pad \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n*smack*\u00A0 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"LordFerret","CreatedById":111598,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-03-07T07:32:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223310091\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022171645\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221520189905\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127483\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022eddiew\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 3/4/2018 at 1:58 PM, eddiew said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nastro-fu\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m writing that one down.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}